5) Create a program where both static and non-static variables are incremented in a method, and analyze the
final values.
-->class Counter {
        static int staticCount = 0;
        int instanceCount = 0;
    
        void increment() {
            staticCount++;
            instanceCount++;
        }
    }
    
    public class Main {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            Counter c1 = new Counter();
            Counter c2 = new Counter();
            Counter c3 = new Counter();
    
            c1.increment();
            c2.increment();
            c3.increment();
    
            System.out.println("Static Count: " + Counter.staticCount);
    
            System.out.println("c1 instance: " + c1.instanceCount);
            System.out.println("c2 instance: " + c2.instanceCount);
            System.out.println("c3 instance: " + c3.instanceCount);
        }
    }
    🔹 Output:
    Static Count: 3
    c1 instance: 1
    c2 instance: 1
    c3 instance: 1

